1.title: Premiere
1.plot: A body is discovered on the pier and the Hennessys and the Kielys are at war again. Meanwhile, Michael Hennessy is hiding something.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: A familiar face returns to the Kiely family, spelling trouble for the Gardaí. Niamh Reid tries to get the café ready for opening.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: A visit to the hospital causes heartbreak for Supt. James McKay and his wife Claire, who remains defiant.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Michael Hennessy's lies catch up with him. Katie's promise to get on with estranged mum Bridget founders.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: A mystery woman causes trouble for Garda Sharon Cleere and her colleague, Paudge. Menawhile at the Kiely household, Katie tries to restore order to the family.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Katie hears some good news but there are still potential problems that could ruin her chances. Patricia is fuming over a financial issue at the pub.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Patricia Hennessy suspects Katie Kiely took the money from the pub and reports her to the Gardaí, but when questioned Katie insists.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Sharon finally confronts Brian with the CCTV footage of him kissing a schoolgirl but he denies everything and has an explanation for what she saw.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: As Bridget bags up Darren's belongings she makes a shocking discovery. Back at the station, Brian unsettles Sharon when he suggests 'stickin.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: An unfortunate coincidence leads to tragic consequences.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Patricia Hennessy extracts the truth from Michael about David's involvement in the death of Darren Kylie.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: The truth about the night of Darren Kiely's death emerges.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: Bully-boy Brian clashes with a local teen tearaway who accuses him of police brutality.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: Brian launches a campaign to save his own skin when faced with a Garda investigation into his conduct.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: Sharon finally confronts schoolgirl Rachel Reid about her underage relationship and urges her to tell her father, Liam.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: As Sharon and Brian respond to a reported break-in at a warehouse, three thugs give Sharon a severe beating while Brian ignores her cries for help.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: Patricia and Claire Hennessy discuss Michael's future with him so that he is prepared for what he may face.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: Sharon Cleere tries to summon the courage to tell the truth about her attack. At the Tyrell's, Tommy accuses Angela of spending too much time at work.

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot: A vulnerable Sharon returns to work but Brian is as determined as ever to see her off his patch. Adrijan and Seán have to deal with 2 public disorder cases.

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: Darkness hangs over Red Rock garda station following the death of an inmate held in the cells.

21.title: Episode #1.21
21.plot: Brian continues his tyranny of Sharon but is left fuming since she refuses to be pushed around.

22.title: Episode #1.22
22.plot: Katie finally discovers the truth about how David was being blackmailed by her brother.

23.title: Episode #1.23
23.plot: Katie's revelations about events surrounding Darren's death shock the Kielys, not least the fact that she was sleeping with the enemy.

24.title: Episode #1.24
24.plot: The Hennessy brothers are questioned following Katie's damning statement about David's involvement with Darren Kiely.

25.title: Episode #1.25
25.plot: Michael Hennessy is taken into custody and the Kielys are overjoyed as they hear of his fate.

26.title: Episode #1.26
26.plot: Nikki and Angela come close to solving the long-standing case of a missing person, but the results prove personally devastating for Angela.

27.title: Episode #1.27
27.plot: Superintendent McKay tells Sharon to take some time off. Brian antagonises her further but this time she snaps and lashes out at him.

28.title: Episode #1.28
28.plot: Sharon's accusations make it a tough day for everyone at Red Rock Garda station.

29.title: Episode #1.29
29.plot: McKay and Tyrell speak to Liam Reid about the accusations made concerning his daughter, Rachel.

30.title: Episode #1.30
30.plot: Liam Reid is refusing to give up on the allegations made against Sergeant Brian McGonigle.

31.title: Episode #1.31
31.plot: Sergeant McGonigle plays the victim with Angela and McKay.

32.title: Episode #1.32
32.plot: Despite Liam's best efforts it appears there is no getting through to troubled teen Rachel Reid who then fails to turn up for school.

33.title: Episode #1.33
33.plot: The Gardaí search for the missing Rachel Reid.

34.title: Episode #1.34
34.plot: The search for Rachel Reid continues as her father seeks answers from the Garda Station.

35.title: Episode #1.35
35.plot: Rachel Reid is still missing and things are taking a toll on her sister Niamh and Dad Liam. In a bid to broaden their hunt for the missing schoolgirl, Detective Sergeant Nikki Grogan and Sergeant Angela Tyrell help the Reids prepare a television appeal. Despite agreeing to do the television appeal, Liam is finding it particularly tough as he tries to put everything into words. Seeing Liam on the brink, Niamh calls in Patricia Hennessy as some welcome support for her dad. Patricia tries to gently talk some sense into Liam, encouraging him not to let Niamh do the appeal...

36.title: Episode #1.36
36.plot: Rachel Reid telephones Brian McGonigle to ask him to run away with her.

37.title: Episode #1.37
37.plot: Rachel Reid contacts Brian McGonigle again, but this time it is more serious, as she has consumed a deadly concoction of vodka and pills.

38.title: Episode #1.38
38.plot: Rachel lies unconscious in the caravan, having taken a cocktail of pills and vodka.

39.title: Episode #1.39
39.plot: As Rachel Reid recovers in hospital following her ordeal, the Gardaí are anxious to speak to her about the sexual allegations.

40.title: Episode #1.40
40.plot: As Rachel Reid is giving her statement about recent events and allegations surrounding Sergeant Brian McGonigle, the sergeant arrives at the station.

41.title: Episode #1.41
41.plot: David Hennessy tries to change Katie Kiely's mind about the baby.

42.title: Episode #1.42
42.plot: With Katie intent on having an abortion, Vincent and Bridget try to stop her.

43.title: Episode #1.43
43.plot: The net closes in on Angela Tyrell's junkie son, Conor, following the recent staged 'robbery'.

44.title: Episode #1.44
44.plot: Katie Kiely is in turmoil as she arrives at the airport. Angela and Tommy Tyrell head home to confront Conor about his drug habit.

45.title: Episode #1.45
45.plot: Troublemaker Ollie Coyne reveals that he has footage proving Paudge was behind the fire in his house while the Gardaí search for Adrijan's hit and run driver.

46.title: Episode #1.46
46.plot: The chief suspect in Adrijan's hit-and-run case is brought in for questioning. Paudge's troubles increase.

47.title: Episode #1.47
47.plot: Katie Kiely attends a baby scan alone and discovers she is expecting a baby boy. However, there are complications with the baby's heart and he will need an operation

59.title: Episode #1.59
59.plot: Pressure mounts on the Gardai to discover who was behind Davey's stabbing.

60.title: Episode #1.60
60.plot: Nikki and Paudge receive a tip-off that Beady's gang are operating from The Goat pub, and Sean and Niamh seem to be finally making progress in the romance stakes.

61.title: Episode #1.61
61.plot: It's Halloween and Angela and Sharon must deal with the ghouls and goblins of St. Columba's flats on a call out. They find themselves the targets of masked local youths, who throw bottles and cans as they try to make their way to a woman who has fallen and trapped in her flat. When they break into the flat, they find Jo Black, not only with a broken ankle but also eight months pregnant and going into labour. Are Angela and Sharon prepared to deliver a baby? Beady isn't the only Burke on the Guards' radar, when Sean nabs Beady's niece Aoife dealing on the Ridge. ...

62.title: Episode #1.62
62.plot: Angela and Sharon are still in a panic at St. Columba's flats. There's no sign of an ambulance and the baby fast is fast approaching. A confident Sharon takes charge and assures scared mum-to-be Jo, that she'll deliver the baby. The two women help an exhausted Jo give birth to a baby girl, but the baby turns blue and unresponsive. Can they also save the newborn's life? Back at the station, Nikki is frantic as the drugs confiscated from Aoife Burke have gone missing on her watch. With no evidence in sight a smug Aoife can walk free, to both Paudge and Beady's relief. ...

63.title: Episode #1.63
63.plot: Pressure is on Adrijan to provide an alibi for his suspicious absence. Crucial evidence has gone missing and McKay won't back down until Adrijan explains his on duty disappearance. Adrijan couldn't have picked a worse time to rendez-vous with his love interest Joan Curry. Worse still admitting to sneaking off to sleep with the widow of a man who died in his custody could leave Adrijan on the firing blocks. Under pressure Adrijan confesses to McKay that he was with a married woman and McKay insists she turn up to the station. Left with no other option and the prospect ...

64.title: Episode #1.64
64.plot: A furious Grainne Webb storms into Red Rock Garda station, refusing to leave until she has seen her son Davey. The Gardaí can't keep Davey locked up and Grainne insists Davey was with her the day of the petrol station robbery. Acting on a personal grudge against the Gardaí and fear of Laser's thugs, Grainne demands Davey stop talking to them. Nikki has built a tight case against Davey, he's already on a suspended sentence and with the CCTV footage, there's enough to charge him. McKay, on the other hand, is having doubts about pushing forward. McKay knows Davey is the ...

65.title: Episode #1.65
65.plot: Things are heating up between Michael Hennessy and his new love interest Siobhan. The pair can't seem to keep their hands off each other to the dismay of Patricia, who is less than impressed when Siobhan tags along to the Hennessy family lunch. Siobhan's not afraid to speak her mind and can't help but rub Patricia up the wrong way. However, Patricia won't have to worry about her son's love life too much longer when Siobhan reveals she's off on her travels again. Poor Michael has fallen hard for her and now she's leaving in a week - can he let the love of his life ...

66.title: Episode #1.66
66.plot: Sirens are blaring as the Gardai of Red Rock round up Beady's associates for questioning. McKay is determined to find out the truth behind the leak in the station but Beady's thugs won't say a word - they know better than to rat on their boss. McKay has relentlessly spent months trying to shut down Beady's drug trade and have him put behind bars, but Beady has evaded McKay at every corner. The Superintendent has hit breaking point and finally hauls Beady into the station. McKay wants to deal with Beady face to face and a cell with no witnesses is the ideal location. ...

67.title: Episode #1.67
67.plot: Enough is enough and McKay calls in the Bureau to shake down the station. There's a rat among the Red Rock Gardaí and he'll find out who it is if it's the last thing he does. Paudge is feeling the heat and realises it's only a matter of time before McKay confronts him. There's no escaping suspicion for Paudge who is the first person to be summoned for an interview with Detective Inspector Dom Kelly. DI Kelly won't go easy on Paudge, can he keep his nerve when asked about his involvement with Beady Burke? Katie's in for a surprise when her one night fling Rory arrives ...

68.title: Episode #1.68
68.plot: Michael's bags are packed and he's prepared to go on the run with Siobhan to Thailand. Siobhan, however, is having doubts and is worried about the consequences of what they are about to do. Michael is awaiting trail for the murder of Darren Kiely, if he leaves the country he can never come back. Can he really live with the harsh reality of a future without his family? Meanwhile Patricia finds Michael's goodbye note in Harbour Haulage and frantically calls Claire and David to help her. They need to get to the airport now or Patricia may never see her son again. Rory ...

69.title: Episode #1.69
69.plot: A taxi robbery has gone horribly wrong and the guards are called out to the scene. A young, dark haired man, with track marks down his arms and no ID has been fatally injured. It dawns on Angela that her son Conor fits the description and she can't help but fear the worst when Conor doesn't answer her call and is a no show at work. Angela frantically runs to the accident, arriving just as the paramedics pull a blanket over the body. All stops still - Angela feels as though her world is about to crash down around her until she realises it isn't Conor's body but rather ...

70.title: Episode #1.70
70.plot: Conor regrets his night spent with Rachel. He was incredibly upset by his friend Dooley's death and tells Rachel that they've made a mistake by taking things too fast. Rachel is furious but it's too late for Conor to apologise. As far as Rachel's concerned he's only a selfish junkie who has taken advantage of her and could have helped Dooley. Rachel's harsh words hit an already distraught Conor hard. With everything falling to pieces around him could Conor be pushed to seek solace in a syringe? CHIS (Covert Human Intelligence Sources) have turned down McKay's request ...

71.title: Episode #1.71
71.plot: There's been a crack down on the Ridge - Beady Burke can't move without the Gardaí breathing down his neck and now McKay's attentions have turned to eliminating Laser Byrne. He's landed with the perfect opportunity to nab the thug when unofficial informant Davey Webb tips McKay off about a van full of fake cigarettes and booze belonging to Laser that he'll be driving. McKay insists Davey refuse, someone else needs to be driving if the guards are going to raid it. Laser doesn't take Davey's refusal well and forces him to be the driver. A panicked Davey rings McKay - ...

72.title: Episode #1.72
72.plot: Sean and Adrijan are alerted to the case of Joanna Jenkins. The pair have already had a run in with Joanna after saving her son Ned from burning down their house while left unattended. She's lost custody of Ned and has gone on the run with him. The lads find Joanna, who has abandoned her son with a friend and is now dangling herself from the railings of a roof threatening to jump. Joanna's been drinking heavily, is distressed and suicidal. Sean suggests they wait for a negotiator but an agitated Adrijan provokes the Joanna and claims she can hardly look after herself,...

73.title: Episode #1.73
73.plot: A hysterical Grainne Webb storms into Red Rock Garda Station demanding to see McKay. Laser Byrne's thugs have been targeting her home and with Davey hiding out in Galway there's nobody to protect her and daughter Chloe. Fearing for their lives, Grainne insists McKay find them somewhere else to live. The best McKay can do is send a patrol car out to the Ridge. Will he be left wishing he did more after news reaches the station that a house on the Ridge has been petrol bombed? There can only have been one target - have Grainne and Chloe made it out alive? The Kiely's are...

74.title: Episode #1.74
74.plot: Abandoned by his mother and under threat from Laser Byrne, Davey Webb seeks protection at McKay's apartment. A guilt ridden McKay can't refuse, he's all Davey has left and feels completely responsible for his safety. Claire insists McKay shows Davey the door, they are risking both their careers - she's his advising solicitor and he's a superintendent acting without authorisation. Davey is furious when McKay suggests he go back to Galway until everything dies down. He wouldn't be in this mess if McKay hadn't convinced him to be his informant. Laser's thugs have killed ...

75.title: Episode #1.75
75.plot: After months of waiting, the Kielys and Hennessys finally come face to face in the courtroom. Emotions run high as each family anxiously awaits Michael's sentencing. He may have secured a plea bargain for the manslaughter of Darren Kiely but it's up to the judge to determine if he'll end up behind bars. Bridget Kiely isn't feeling confident, there's no chance a judge will pick their side over the Hennessys. Vinnie struggles putting pen to paper for the victim impact statement. It's vital they get it right - this is their last chance to get justice for Darren. ...

76.title: Episode #1.76
76.plot: Each family is left reeling in the aftermath of Michael's sentencing. Patricia insists the Hennessys go to the Pier Pub for a drink, they need it after the day they've had. She can't believe her son is going to jail and wonders if they could have done more to prevent it. The Kielys are furious with the result, how can the man who killed their son not go down for life? The justice system has completely failed them - it's one rule for people like the Hennessys and one rule for the Kielys. Left with no other choice, Vincent decides to seek his own brand of justice and ...

77.title: Episode #1.77
77.plot: A dark cloud hangs over the Kielys who are about to spend their first Christmas without Darren. Michael Hennessy might be spending the next year in a prison cell but they will never get their son back. Overwhelmed by grief Vincent realises that the only way to get justice for Darren is if he does something. An eye for an eye - a son for a son. Amid the Christmas cheer, Michael is left alone in Harbour Haulage finalising business before starting his prison sentence. There's a sudden power outage but when he goes to investigate, Michael's left facing down the barrel of ...

78.title: Episode #1.78
78.plot: Vincent comes face to face with Michael Hennessy - the man who killed his son. His gun is unwavering, this is for Darren. Michael pleads with Vincent to put it down. He didn't mean to kill Darren and if he could change what happened that night he would. Vincent's mind is set, the courts have failed him and this is his chance to even the score. The pair are interrupted by a message on the answering machine. It's David gushing about the birth of his baby boy, Michael needs to get to the hospital now. Michael appeals to Vincent, can he kill his grandson's uncle? Does he ...

79.title: Episode #1.79
79.plot: McKay and Claire are on cloud nine with the news that Claire is expecting. The flutter of a tiny heartbeat at the ultrasound, has the pair in complete awe. Claire and McKay have never been happier - they can finally start the family they've always longed for. Despite his overwhelming joy, there's something McKay just can't ignore any longer. The unsuccessful raids, drugs going missing, Beady evading conviction at every corner, Paudge is corrupt and McKay knows it, he's always known it. The moment Paudge's spent months evading is finally here. The cuffs are out and ...

80.title: Episode #1.80
80.plot: Red Rock is in shock, a resident has been murdered and the station is on high alert. A massive manhunt has been called to track down the assailant who is quickly and carefully covering their tracks, the weapon is dumped and their clothes are destroyed. Fortunately the horrific incident has been caught on CCTV and there's a witness, will this be enough for detective Nikki to piece together who did it and why? One thing's for sure, Red Rock will never be the same again.

54.title: Episode #2.54
54.plot: David's been released without charge, much to the immense anger of the Kielys. As the severe gravity of his own actions dawn on David, he realizes that the only way to put things right is to speak to Katie and convince her of his innocence. However, David could quickly live to regret this decision when confronted with an armed Vinnie and Keith ready to serve their own brand of justice. The Hennessy brothers beat Darren to death and now it's time for the Kielys to do the same. An eye for an eye, a brother for a brother. Heavily pregnant Claire's waters have broken in ...

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: The Gardaí believe they've finally apprehended the murder suspect. All eyes are on Davey Webb who has been brought in for questioning. With CCTV footage and a murder weapon, Nikki won't be backing down until she has a confession. However, Claire has Davey trained well and he won't be admitting to anything anytime soon. A dishevelled and guilt ridden Paudge returns to Red Rock Garda Station. He's gotten wind that Davey's been arrested but is reluctant to believe that the young lad was the behind the murder. Davey's a good kid and should have never gotten messed up in ...

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: Initially intrigued by his dangerous past, Rachel is starting to feel frustrated with Conor who seems more focused on getting his next hit than paying attention to her. The pair rendezvous, with Conor promising that this date will be all about her. However, when he disappears mid-date Rachel isn't surprised when he finds him down an alleyway with a dealer. Enough is enough, can she really continue chasing after Conor as he chases after heroin? Sharon makes an earth-shattering discovery when she decides to search Paudge's locker. He's been on edge for weeks, lashing ...

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: Months of hiding, months of secrecy and lies have come to a head. Paudge can't live with himself any longer. He needs to tell Nikki about his involvement with Beady. The guilt has been eating him up, he confessed to McKay but now it's time for everyone to know.Rachel faces the harsh reality of life with a heroin addict. She arrives at the Pipes to meet with Conor whose only concern is taking his next hit. Conor relaxes as soon as he shoots up but when he goes suddenly cold and lifeless, it's up to Rachel to save him. The body of a familiar face is found on wasteland ...

7.title: Episode #3.7
7.plot: Angela is heartbroken following Conor's near fatal overdose. She's come dangerously close to losing her son to heroin and will do everything in her power to ensure that doesn't happen again. As far as Angela is concerned Conor's only chance now is to go cold turkey and it's up to her and Tommy to watch him life a hawk. When duty calls for Angela at the station, it's up to Tommy to keep an eye on Conor but when he suddenly has to rush to Stephen's school he's left with a dilemma. Can Conor really be trusted to be left home alone? Detective Rory has never been afraid to...

8.title: Episode #3.8
8.plot: Brian McGonigle is back with an unexpected return that's set to send shockwaves throughout the whole of Red Rock. Last we saw of the fallen cop he was being carted out of the station after a well-deserved punch from Superintendent McKay. Following months of bullying Sharon and his illicit and manipulative relationship with Rachel Reid, does Brian have a death wish returning to town as Red Rock's most hated figure? Alone and upset Rachel has skipped school to drown her sorrows in a local park. Her and Conor are officially over, having come to the realisation that ...

9.title: Episode #3.9
9.plot: Brian's back in town and eager to reconnect with his estranged family. He's determined to clear his name and prove to them that everything that's been said about his affair with Rachel was a lie. A meeting with his daughter Mel, Rachel's former best friend, is abruptly cut short when his wife, Jules storms in on their conversation outside a café. Brian has some neck coming back into their lives after all the trouble that he has caused. Sharon is left shaking after the disturbance she's called to break up turns out to be between Brian and his wife. Coming face to face ...

10.title: Episode #3.10
10.plot: Tensions are running high between Sean and Adrijan following Adrijan's assault on a suspect. With Claire Hennessy as the suspects defence Adrijan could face a potential brutality charge. Sean's convinced he was out of line but when interrogated by Nikki will he stick up for his best friend's claim of self defence? Rachel is desperate to deny her feelings for Brian. She ignores his persistent calls but can she hold her nerve when he tracks her down. With no one else to turn to, Rachel struggles to resist him when he invites her around to his flat to talk. Tommy steps ...

11.title: Episode #3.11
11.plot: With Brian McGonigle firmly settled back in Red Rock, Liam can't help but fear the worst - could Rachel go running back into the arms of the fallen guard? Much to his surprise and relief, there's only been one guy on Rachel's mind these days, Conor Tyrell. Brian's been side lined by a younger model and Rachel's eager to make a proper go of her relationship with Conor. However, in a desperate moment could Conor risk everything by asking Rachel to score heroin for him? The Tyrell's have been pushed to breaking point as going cold turkey takes an extreme toll on Conor. ...

12.title: Episode #3.12
12.plot: Tommy and Angela are at each other's throats over Conor's addiction. Tommy insists their only option is to control his heroin intake themselves and slowly wean him off it but Angela won't stand for becoming her son's dealer. Their only chance as a family is if they get away from Red Rock and soon. Angela requests a transfer but Nikki's not going to lose one of her best officers without a damn good reason. She's kept it a secret so long, will Angela finally crack under the pressure and open up to Nikki about her son's addiction? Rachel has hit breaking point with Conor...

13.title: Episode #3.13
13.plot: Liam's suspicions are at an all time high. Rachel's been skipping school and her excuses aren't quite adding up. Rachel can't be seeing Brian behind his back - can she? Desperate to confront the man who seduced his daughter, Liam demands Detective Nikki hand over his address. If the Gardaí aren't going to do anything about Brian, he will. David's completely devastated when he accidentally finds out that the Kiely's have been planning a christening for baby Luke without him. David can't stand being pushed out of his son's life anymore and this is the last straw. Sean ...

14.title: Episode #3.14
14.plot: A furious Brian McGonigle shows his beaten and bruised face at Red Rock Garda station. Someone's leaked his address, putting his life in danger and he won't be backing down until he finds out who's to blame. Sean's fears are realized when he discovers Adrijan passed out drunk in the cells. He's in no fit state to be interviewed by the Garda Ombudsman and it's up to Sean to act quick to stop it going ahead by any means possible. Could Sean be pushed to desperate measures to protect his friend? Patricia has extravagant plans for baby Luke's christening much to the ...

15.title: Episode #3.15
15.plot: With his trial only a matter of weeks away and time behind bars looming, Brian has Rachel hooked on his every word. If she wants a future together, Rachel needs to recant her statement and tell Nikki that everything she ever told her was a lie - Brian never slept with her. Rachel is hesitant to go ahead with the plan, this could destroy her relationship with Liam forever, but Brian insists it's now or never. He chose her over his family, can she be pushed to do the same? Danger is lurking behind every corner of the Ridge and Sean and Adrijan had better watch their ...

16.title: Episode #3.16
16.plot: All eyes are on Rachel as she awaits interrogation by Nikki. Liam's desperate attempt to drag his daughter out of the station before saying anything she may regret is futile. Rachel won't be backing down until Nikki listens to her, not when her future with Brian is at stake. Once she recants her statement there'll be no going back for Rachel, is she really prepared to say she was lying about Brian all along? With Rachel safely tucked away in the Garda Station, Brian can finally make his move and worm his way back into his family's life. As Sean hangs on for dear life ...

17.title: Episode #3.17
17.plot: Liam's been shaken to the core by Rachel's sudden decision to recant her statement. Brian's successfully wormed his way back into his daughter's mind and she must be lying to protect him - there can be no other explanation. Rachel swears Brian never touched her but Liam refuses to believe her. He knows when his daughter is lying - all he needs is proof. Sean might be on the road to recovery but Adrijan is still racked with guilt after coming dangerously close to losing his best friend. The ambush on Sean can only have been at the hands of Jack O'Reilly. However, when ...

18.title: Episode #3.18
18.plot: Spiralling further and further into a state of paranoia, Liam appears to have lost all trust in Rachel, convinced she must be seeing Brian behind his back. After a quick snoop in her phone throws up nothing, will Liam resort to desperate measures and see no other option but to spy his own daughter? With the christening on the horizon, Patricia is more determined than ever to have Luke's last name changed to Hennessy. It's his birth right after all and her only chance at preventing the Kielys from pushing David out of his son's life any further. However, could this be ...

19.title: Episode #3.19
19.plot: The day of the christening has arrived, forcing the feuding Kielys and Hennessys to finally play nice for the sake of baby Luke. After weeks of meticulous planning, Patricia is determined the celebrations will go off without a hitch but wherever the Kielys go trouble is sure to follow. Could all hell break loose when an unwanted guest makes a surprise appearance much to the horror of Bridget? Sean Holden is back in action, making a triumphant return to the station following his recent assault. His fellow officers are delighted to see him, all except one - Adrijan. The...

20.title: Episode #3.20
20.plot: Rachel's no where to be found and there's no doubt in Liam's mind that she must be with Brian. Determined to catch the pair in the act Liam drives furiously to Brian's bedsit, only to be stopped by Nikki. Last time Liam confronted him, Brian walked away with a bloody face and there's no saying how far he could go this time. Following the drama in the Pier Pub, Katie and David seek refuge away from the commotion at the Hennessys. Will old feelings be reignited as the pair enjoy a rare intimate moment alone? Vinnie is furious with Bridget, who he suspects of having an ...

21.title: Episode #3.21
21.plot: Rachel struggles to contain her fury and heartbreak after discovering Brian's been meeting with his wife behind her back. She has no time for his desperate pleas and insistence that nothing is going on with his ex. It's clear that Brian will go to any lengths to get what he wants. It looks like Rachel is finally starting to see through his lies once and for all! Time's up for Bridget who desperately needs to pay back her loans to Joe Fallon and fast. In a last ditch attempt she drafts in Vinnie to help source the cash. No stranger to dodgy dealings, Vinnie's lined up ...

22.title: Episode #3.22
22.plot: Bridget needs to face the music with loan shark Joe Fallon. Last minute nerves get the better of the usually unfaltering Bridget who begs Vinnie to go in her place. They Kielys might think coughing up the cash will keep Fallon off their backs for good but Joe isn't about to let Bridget walk out of his life that easy. For once things are looking up for Conor Tyrell - He's gotten his job back at The Neptune and his friendship with Rachel appears to be back on track or so he thinks. Conor begins to see a change in Rachel's behaviour and is convinced she's back under ...

23.title: Episode #3.23
23.plot: Brian's bedsit has been the target of a ransacking. Detective Rory is dispatched to investigate the scene but with a list of enemies as long as Brian's anyone could be a potential suspect. However, some surprising evidence suggest the culprit is a lot closer to home...An unsuspecting Sharon is rocked by an accusation that could land her in jeopardy. Defiant in her innocence, Sharon insists she's nothing to hide but is she about to speak too soon? It's Bridget's first day at the beck and call of Joe Fallon where she's quickly confronted with the harsh reality of ...

24.title: Episode #3.24
24.plot: Brian has the evidence stacked high and is determined to have Sharon held responsible for ransacking his bedsit. She has the means and motive but can he convince a highly suspicious Nikki that she's behind it? Joe insists a reluctant Bridget join him for a private business lunch at a luxury hotel. It's no surprise when the client fails to make an appearance, conveniently leaving Joe and Bridget to enjoy the room to themselves. Joe clearly has an ulterior motive, but can Bridget resist his charms? Sharon and Paudge are called to the bedside of Ger McIntyrne who has ...

25.title: Episode #3.25
25.plot: With his trial date looming, Brian's intent on clearing his name and isn't afraid to destroy anyone who gets in his way. He's finally gotten the upper hand on a distraught Sharon who is facing suspension after being framed for ransacking his bedsit. One act of revenge down, Brian has his sights firmly set on his next target - Angela Tyrell. Bridget's desperate to avoid loan shark Joe following their close encounter at the hotel. Joe's persistent advances make Bridget's skin crawl and besides that she just can't be disloyal to Vinnie. Joe smells a rat when Bridget ...

26.title: Episode #3.26
26.plot: Angela is left shaken to her very core by a revelation that could see her family torn apart all at the hands of Brian. Despite having worked side by side with him for years, Brian will do whatever it takes to ensure his freedom. He has the evidence and is prepared to take former friend Angela down in one fell swoop if she doesn't co-operate. With her career and son's future on the line, has Angela been left with no other option but to back up Brian? Paudge does all he can to cheer Sharon up as her life is turned upside down following her suspension. He can't stand ...

27.title: Episode #3.27
27.plot: Sharon's world has been left in tatters at the hands of Brian who has relished in making her life a misery since his return to Red Rock. Suspended from duty and terrified to be home alone, Sharon has reached breaking point with his torment. However, she better had watch her back, as Brian just can't resist coming face to face with her one last time before the court case... Reeling from the fact that Brian is blackmailing his mum and has photographic evidence of both Tommy and him scoring drugs, Conor confronts Rachel in a desperate bid to save his family. Given their ...

28.title: Episode #3.28
28.plot: Desperate to save his daughter from Brian's clutches, Liam drags Rachel to the Garda station believing he's finally caught her red handed trying to run away with Brian. Does Liam have all the evidence he needs to have Brian banged up at long last? Conor plays a disappearing act, leaving Tommy to frantically track him down before he does something stupid. Enraged by Brian's blackmail threats against his mother, and determined to prevent him destroying his family's future, Conor decides to take matters into his own hands once and for all. Paudge will go to any lengths ...

29.title: Episode #3.29
29.plot: Brian's day of reckoning has arrived with the start of his court case. With Brian's freedom on the line, it's time for a troubled Rachel to take the stand. Can she keep up her months of lies or will she crack under oath? At the Garda Station, Nikki rallies her troops - after all their hard work this could finally be the day they send down Brian. Just as she's about to leave for court, a crucial piece of evidence lands on her lap that could turn everything on its head, potentially bringing the whole trial to a sudden halt. An anxious Sharon must also take the stand, ...

30.title: Episode #3.30
30.plot: Red Rock is on high alert as Nikki launches a man hunt for Brian. Every guard available has been despatched to track him down and Nikki won't give up until he's dragged kicking and screaming into her station. However, with each new lead being knocked back as quickly as the next one appears, has the scheming Brian given Nikki the slip for good? Angela anxiously waits for Conor as he faces a harsh interrogation by Rory. Angela had better watch her back as Nikki makes a shocking discovery about her and Brian that could land her job in jeopardy. Shaken by recent events ...

31.title: Episode #3.31
31.plot: No stone has been left unturned as Nikki continues her frantic manhunt for Brian. Much to Sharon's relief, a crucial piece of evidence is discovered, finally vindicating her for the ransacking of Brian's bedsit. However, with no clear sign of him having fled the country yet, a hell bent Nikki is convinced that it's only matter of time before he slips up and she can finally nab him. With Brian on the loose Liam is worried for his daughter's safety, insisting Rachel stay off school so he can keep a close eye on her. There is no chance in hell he'll be letting Brian get ...

33.title: Episode #3.33
33.plot: Tommy's life hangs dangerously in the balance when he's rushed to hospital. A distraught Conor is left feeling completely responsible, have his actions left his father fighting for his life? Angela and youngest son Stephen hold a bedside vigil but only time will tell if Tommy makes it through. Can Angela ever forgive Conor if she loses her husband? At the station, Nikki is hit with yet another set back when faced with the sudden disappearance of Brian's daughter Mel McGonigle. With Brian still seemingly on the run. There can only be one possible explanation, she's run...

34.title: Episode #3.34
34.plot: Nikki makes an explosive discovery in the search for Brian's whereabouts, sending shockwaves throughout the whole of Red Rock. As everyone in the station comes to terms with the sudden development, it appears as though Sharon has been hit hardest by the unexpected revelation. Having spent weeks as the prime target of Brian's torment, Sharon's life has been slowly destroyed in Brian's manipulative efforts to redeem himself and get his life back. Clearly shaken by the turn of events, it comes as no surprise when Nikki questions Sharon's ability to remain on the job. ...

35.title: Episode #3.35
35.plot: Determined to leave no stone unturned, a hell bent Nikki resorts to questioning her own officers in her most recent investigation. Nobody is beyond suspicion not even Sharon and Paudge. The pair come face to face with Nikki and Rory and they had better get their stories straight or it could be their jobs on the line. Despite her protests, Nikki is left with no other choice but to take Sharon off the investigation. Could Sharon's worst fear come to light, has Brian finally done enough to convince everyone that she's not a good cop? Adrijan's life could be in grave ...

36.title: Episode #3.36
36.plot: Back at the station, Sharon has grown increasingly jumpy and paranoid since the discovery of Brian's body. Her unusual behaviour has not gone unnoticed by a worried Paudge. As far as he's concerned Sharon should be jumping for joy, the man who tormented her for months is gone and there's no way he can come back to haunt her. However, when left to re-examine CCTV footage Sharon had been working on, Paudge stumbles upon someShocking evidence that could have grave consequences for his partner. Paudge now faces the terrible possibility that Sharon is Brian's killer. The ...

37.title: Episode #3.37
37.plot: The day of Brian's funeral has arrived, as everyone prepares to say one last final goodbye to Brian. Much to the dismay of Nikki's team, Superintendent Dunne has insisted the Gardaí show a united front and attend the funeral. Brian was never convicted, he is still one of their own and they need to show their support. However, after all that Sharon has been through with Brian, there's no way in hell she's helping lay to rest the man who tried to destroy her life. Meanwhile a tormented Rachel struggles to come to terms with the loss of Brian. As far as she's concerned ...

38.title: Episode #3.38
38.plot: Detective Rory's hunch has led to one the biggest breakthroughs in the murder investigation so far. Blood at the scene confirms it - Brian was killed at a disused warehouse know locally as The Pipes. However, the smile is quickly wiped from Rory's face when confronted by Nikki, who is furious that he went behind her back with the break to score points with Superintendent Dunne. Next time he gets a lead he reports to her first - this is her station and her investigation, not Dunne's!Angered by Rory's subordinance, Nikki decides to take matters into her own hands with ...

39.title: Episode #3.39
39.plot: All eyes are on Liam Reid who has been dragged into the station for interrogation. Rory's discovered some incriminating evidence and believes they've finally caught Brian's killer red handed. New CCTV footage from the night of the murder has arrived and Liam's unusual behaviour appears suspicious at best. Despite Nikki's reluctance, Rory can see the holes in Liam's alibi and is convinced if they put enough pressure on him he'll crack. It's only a matter of time. Vicious Joe Fallon has his claws into Bridget and refuses to release her from her debt. It seems this ...

40.title: Episode #3.40
40.plot: Bridget is still on edge following her horrific encounter with Joe Fallon. An enraged Vinnie refuses to sit idly by and let Fallon go unpunished, but Bridget insists they need to be smarter than the loan shark and hit him where it hurts most. Before anything goes down, Katie and baby Luke are sent out of harm's way. If they're launching an attack on Joe they can't risk putting their own lives on the line too. Armed and ready, Bridget, Vinnie and Keith put their plan into action - there's no going back now. It's time to fight fire with fire. The strain of leading a ...

41.title: Episode #3.41
41.plot: After successfully pulling off their revenge plan, the Kielys have handed the Gardaí everything they need and more to convict Joe Fallon. Now all they have to do is sit tight until he's out of their lives forever. They don't have to wait too long before Keith spots Detective Rory launching a raid on the loan shark's office and warehouse. Joe can either come to the station voluntarily or he's getting arrested on the spot - it's his choice. A furious Joe soon realises that he's been stitched up by the Kielys and he's going to make sure they pay, if it's the last thing ...

42.title: Episode #3.42
42.plot: The Tyrells are faced with the severe gravity of their situation when Angela, Tommy and Conor are all landed as prime suspects in the investigation of Brian's murder. Angela's world has suddenly fallen apart around her and she can't help but feel like a criminal in her own station as she prepares to face harsh interrogation by Nikki. Feeling betrayed by her own best friend, Nikki won't back down until Angela tells her the truth - once and for all. Detective Rory believes he's successfully backed Tommy into a corner. Brian was harassing his wife and tormenting his ...

21.title: Episode #4.21
21.plot: Sharon convinces Robbie to turn against Laser. As Sharon and Rory transport Robbie to a safehouse (Dunedin), they're ambushed and Robbie is hauled away. Sean and his new partner, Ash Cahill, get off on the wrong foot, when they mistake a doll locked in a car for a baby. Claire's disgusted with Patricia's lies when she learns Michael didn't start the fire. When Patricia shows Claire her bruised neck and explains Michael was transporting drugs, Claire's aghast.

24.title: Episode #4.24
24.plot: Rory sends a coded message to Laser that his place is bugged. Laser orders Rory to sort the bug and Sharon out, or he'll do it - and kill Rory too. Sharon and Rory kiss. Ash and Paudge find Aoife Burke trespassing in a condemned building. Ash lets her off and tells her she'll ask around about Donna. Bridget discovers that Keith is skimming money from the family business after she wrongly accuses Carmel Donovan for having outstanding arrears. Bridget's shocked to learn that Keith did a job for Laser and sacks him from the family business.

25.title: Episode #4.25
25.plot: Refusing to back down without a fight, Jim confronts a gang of thuggish youngsters who have been tourmenting him day and night.

26.title: Episode #4.26
26.plot: Rory shoots Laser, and as he dies, Sharon demands to know what happened to Robbie. Laser whispers something in her ear. Rory finds what he thinks is Jim's gun in Laser's van. With Laser dead, Patricia's forced by David to come clean to Johno about Michael. Johno, unimpressed, insists she reports it. Sharon and Rory sleep together. He convinces her to lie to GSOC. Sharon remembers what Laser said to her: "Ask him" (Rory?!). Ash discovers that Bridget harassed Carmel for money.

27.title: Episode #4.27
27.plot: The gun Rory took from Laser's van isn't Jim's. He returns to where he killed Robbie to look for it, but Ash and Paudge find it before he does. Bridget's rattled when Ash confronts her over claiming benefits while moneylending. Vincent and Bridget clash over what Keith should do with Laser's stolen drugs. Sharon learns that the man who stabbed Rory during his "shining light" case was an associate of Laser.

28.title: Episode #4.28
28.plot: Rory manages to wipe Jim's gun clean of Jim's fingerprints. Sharon confronts Rory over Laser. He maintains he killed Laser to save Sharon and to get Laser back for the "shining light" case. Sharon goes to Dunne and makes a complaint against Rory for "working with Laser Byrne." Vincent despairs when Keith reckons that all he needs to do is sell Laser's drugs fast. Keith proves to Eugene that he's not a rat by assaulting Johno.

29.title: Episode #4.29
29.plot: Rory's gun is taken from him and he's told to take time off. Rory tries to speak to Sharon about her allegation, but she remains resolute. Jim makes the ultimate sacrifice to save Rory by convincing the guards he was Laser's mole, not Rory. Sharon fears she's lost Rory. Bridget badgers Keith to pursue drug dealing, so to get her off his back, Keith pretends to destroy the drugs. Patricia learns her apartments are worthless and is affronted when she's not invited to a Drugs Awareness Ball.

30.title: Episode #4.30
30.plot: A search of the woods throws up a shocking revelation for Sharon.

31.title: Episode #4.31
31.plot: A decomposed body is uncovered where the foot was found. Dunne's horrified to learn it's Donna Burke. Dunne oversteps the mark while interviewing Tony Doyle. Callaghan berates Dunne for worrying about calling off Donna Burke's search. Dunne's aghast at Callaghan's attitude. Ash explains she didn't say anything about Dunne as she didn't want people thinking he'd give her an easy time. Paudge is miffed that Sharon never told him she'd applied to the SDU. Upset and drunk, he snogs Linda. Sharon learns that Jim was at a funeral/wake on the day that Robbie was killed. ...

32.title: Episode #4.32
32.plot: When Sharon learns there are no prints on Jim's gun, she confronts Rory. Rory breaks down and admits everything. Rory asserts that if Sharon says anything about him, he'll reveal that Paudge was Beady Burke's mole. Sharon doesn't expose Rory in order to protect Paudge. Sharon tells Paudge she's leaving the guards. Paudge is heartbroken. Sharon leaves Red Rock to investigate corrupt guards. Paudge wakes up at Linda's. He insults her by hoping nothing happened. Hurt, Linda reveals he slept in her spare bedroom. Sarah Dunne finds Dunne's school ring in his tux.

1.title: Episode #5.1
1.plot: An apathetic Paudge is struggling following Sharon's departure, but a grieving Aoife Burke re-engages him. Keith is tired of living in fear and confronts Alice Bruton.

2.title: Episode #5.2
2.plot: Paudge discovers the extent of Aoife's past with Tony Doyle. Keith pays Alice less than they had agreed.

3.title: Episode #5.3
3.plot: A horrified Dunne learns that the man he is protecting is not who he thought he was. Alice reveals Keith's dealings to the Kielys. Conor wants a chat with Angela at the station.

4.title: Episode #5.4
4.plot: Dunne sweats when Donna's phone leads Angela to the murder site. Ash does her best to prove herself having lost Angela's trust. Keith tries to get a grip on his situation.
